  <summary>3/12/1987--Introduced.
Amends the Trade Act of 1974 to grant eligibility for trade adjustment assistance to firms (and workers in firms) which: (1) explore for, produce, or process oil or natural gas; or (2) provide essential parts or services to other firms that engage in such activities.</summary>
